r treatment, whereas in the IGF-1 group, 66.7% (95% CI, 52.9&#x02013;78.6%) of patients showed hearing improvement (Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab4" ref-type="table">4</xref>). The null hypothesis for the primary outcome was not rejected (<italic>P</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;0.109). However, a trend was observed in the higher proportion of patients in the IGF-1 group showing complete or marked recovery (30&#x000a0;dB or greater in pure-tone average hearing thresholds) over that in the Dex group (Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab2" ref-type="table">2</xref>).<table-wrap id="Tab4"><label>Table 4</label><caption><p>
